cret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?resize=300%2C35\u0026amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?resize=150%2C17\u0026amp;ssl=1 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn a quiet farmhouse outside Waukesha, Wisconsin, Melanie wrote by kerosene lamp. The war had ended, but not the distance. Bernice was gone—moved away, changed, out of reach. They had exchanged letters before, cautiously coded with care and longing. But Melanie couldn’t bring herself to send this one.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn that night in 1944, Melanie had planned to visit. Instead, she stayed home and did laundry, soaking clothes in a wooden tub—trying to push the ache out of her hands and into the water. But she couldn’t escape the memory of Bernice’s voice, or the weight of promises she never kept.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis letter—creased, crumpled, never mailed—was her final confession. She tucked it inside a book of poems and never looked at it again.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"46\" data-attachment-id=\"48438\" data-permalink=\"https://postsecret.com/2025/04/06/sunday-secrets-550/barcode-63/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?fit=400%2C46\u0026amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"400,46\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;1\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"barcode\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?fit=300%2C35\u0026amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?fit=400%2C46\u0026amp;ssl=1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?resize=400%2C46\u0026amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?w=400\u0026amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?resize=300%2C35\u0026amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?resize=150%2C17\u0026amp;ssl=1 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e—email—\u003cbr/\u003eDear Frank,\u003cbr/\u003ethe pleasure and wonder of PostSecret has always been the human connection, human words and human efforts on both sides. The use of AI takes away from that. The effort we put into creating narratives and seeking understanding for your writers should be no less than what they have put into writing to you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"46\" data-attachment-id=\"48438\" data-permalink=\"https://postsecret.com/2025/04/06/sunday-secrets-550/barcode-63/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/postsecret.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/barcode.jpg?fit=400%2C46\u0026amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"400,46\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34